k), then make a gnome and master tinkering, then make a druid to port around for trades, making cash off ports and tracking rares.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 10:18:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you make all that plat?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> *cough* done the camp crap, and for some damn reason as unlucky as I am I never get the loot =\ its always NBG and for some reason everyone elses gear is supposidly worse than mine, so the nice guy comes out in me, and I let them have it, so just like in RL and in game I am to damn nice I guess =\ <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Um...  sorry, but pick-up groups should <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> never</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be NBG.  Not even a little bit.<br><br>Why should my Paladin (for example) ever bother to go help a group camp the GEBs if there's no chance of me getting anything but some XP (and a poor amount, compared to regular camps) out of it?<br><br>Why should a Wizard (for example) ever bother to go help a group camp for Lammys if there's no chance of him getting anything but some XP out of it?  He's much better off getting into an AoE group, after all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscico