<br><br>If nobody in the group would use the item, then sure..go for open roll.  But if you want an item for your twink, then buy it, camp it by yourself or people that agree with your method of open rolling on everything, or level your twink up and camp it with them.<br><br>Just remember, Karma is real.  If you're a wizard and demand rolling on a haste cloak, don't whine when a warrior demands rolling on a wizard spell you need for his level 14 twink wizard.<br><br>/calm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ualferogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alfe Rogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 11:18:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you make all that plat?</span><hr size=1> Please lets not make this a flame thread. I want to know what individual people do to earn there money, so everyone will benefit over this thread. We all know the easy way MOB_020_drops_uber item, we all roll on it. person_03 sells to person_67 for 50k. I want to know like trade skillz which benefit the best, with luclin out, there is alot of crap out there that defeated the market for alot of tradeskillz, and most people cant sit in the market and sell/buy crap all day. So please tell tell if what you do to make plat is any different then anyone else does =\ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugnomgue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gnomgue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 11:34:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you make all that plat?</span><hr size=1> ---------<br>Why should my Paladin (for example) ever bother to go help a group camp the GEBs if there's no chance of me getting anything but some XP (and a poor amount, compared to regular camps) out of it?<br><br>Why should a Wizard (for example) ever bother to go help a group camp for Lammys if there's no chance of him getting anything but some XP out of it? He's much better off getting into an AoE group, after all. <br>---------<br>Since you want to make this an NBG discussion, lets go ahead and do just that.  Why should your paladin ever go to camp GEBs?  Because it is good exp and a break from all the idiots you have to deal with in standard exp zones like velketors, FG, sebilis, etc.  And, if you aren't getting good exp killing the level 46-48 imps in efreeti, it is probably because paladins are worthless in exp groups and contribute nothing but bad dps unless they are outfitted in excellent equipment -- I'm sure everyone else would see much better exp when YOU left )<br><br>And as far as the wizard comment, you do understand that wizards are the LAST thing you need for a standard melee kill group, right?  In fact, they are pretty much a waste of a group slot as a druid makes a better snare/evac due to the fact they can heal, and your example is irrelevent because snare/evac isn't needed in necro/guardian camp.  <br><br>If you're going to make examples like this, please make them relevent.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaphyd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aphyd</A>